sentences: Mansi (Clemensa) Barberis (1899–1986) was a Romanian violinist, music educator, conductor, and composer.
Barberis graduated from the Conservatory in 1922.
In 1936 she also studied voice briefly in Vienna with Max Reger.
Itinerar dacic (1976) to verses by playwright Dominic Stancu
Destin de poet (1981) to verses by Mihai Eminescu
Rondelurile rozelor (1982) song cycle to verses by Alexandru MacedonskiBarberis published an autobiography, Din zori până în amurg (From Dawn until Dusk)

She returned to Romania after a year and took professional employment, but later continued her studies in Paris during three sessions, studying voice, conducting, opera, composition and orchestration.
